<paragraph id="A96E36B1991E80224AD55D97FE906036" blockId="19.[101,1032,190,1059]" pageId="19" pageNumber="432">
Comments. Bra 
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA3991E80224B205D97FDA667F9" box="[336,548,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="432">chystethus vexillum</emphasis>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D32991E8022497F5D97FC0067F9" authorityName="Bolívar" authorityYear="1879" box="[783,898,981,1004]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA3991E8022497F5D97FC0067F9" box="[783,898,981,1004]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="432">B. tricolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The dorsal color pattern, with yellow stripes, and the globose pygophore distinguish this species from 
<emphasis id="9BA5EAA3991E80224AEF5A4EFE906036" box="[159,274,1036,1059]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="432">
<taxonomicName id="6ED14D32991E80224AEF5A4EFE8C6036" authorityName="Bolívar" authorityYear="1879" box="[159,270,1036,1059]" class="Insecta" family="Pentatomidae" genus="Brachystethus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="432" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tricolor">B. tricolor</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
